- Same reason we weren't invited to the rest.

226
00:18:16.156 --> 00:18:18.647
You can't go to a kids' party without a kid.

227
00:18:19.618 --> 00:18:24.494
Being a parent is power and once you're
in that circle you keep everyone else out.

228
00:18:24.665 --> 00:18:30.668
Flo. being a parent is about sharing.
It's about a mom. a dad and a kid.

229
00:18:30.838 --> 00:18:36.213
Except there isn't going to be a kid. Ben.
It's just you and me forever.

230
00:18:40.849 --> 00:18:44.384
- Why can't we adopt?
- We've been through this!

231
00:18:44.561 --> 00:18:49.270
I know. but we have so much love to give.
Why waste it on these stupid pets?

232
00:18:49.441 --> 00:18:51.849
They are not stupid!

233
00:18:52.027 --> 00:18:53.735
Hello!

234
00:18:53.904 --> 00:18:58.732
Think of it this way. All those mothers
had to make do with what nature gave them.

235
00:18:58.909 --> 00:19:02.694
You and I get to pick out our kid.
It'll be like shopping.

236
00:19:02.872 --> 00:19:05.908
- Shopping?
- Uh-huh.

237
00:19:06.084 --> 00:19:09.784
But the neighbours will know we've adopted.
What'll they say?

238
00:19:09.963 --> 00:19:13.249
The neighbours? They'll say. "Look!"

239
00:19:13.425 --> 00:19:18.301
"There's Ben and Flo Healy going out to
yet another birthday party with their new son!"

240
00:19:18.472 --> 00:19:20.761
"Isn't he adorable?"

241
00:19:20.933 --> 00:19:24.717
"And look at how fantastic Flo looks
in her new dress!"

242
00:19:24.895 --> 00:19:28.181
"Where did she get a bag
to match those shoes?"

243
00:19:28.357 --> 00:19:32.521
Then they'll say.
"Let's invite that Healy family over for dinner."

244
00:19:32.695 --> 00:19:35.317
Oh. Ben. dinners!

245
00:19:35.490 --> 00:19:38.242
OK. let's get a kid.

246
00:19:38.576 --> 00:19:41.661
Hurry up. students.
Five more minutes for your pen-pals.

247
00:19:41.746 --> 00:19:44.582
Then we have to work on our times tables.

248
00:19:46.084 --> 00:19:51.327
<i>Dear Queen Elizabeth. how is England?
It must be nice to be a queen.</i>

249
00:19:51.507 --> 00:19:54.294
<i>Dear Bishop Tutu. how are you?</i>

250
00:19:54.468 --> 00:19:58.513
<i>I am fine. I hope everything's going
well with your marching.</i>

251
00:19:58.681 --> 00:20:00.923
<i>Dear Bow Tie Killer. how's prison?</i>

252
00:20:01.100 --> 00:20:06.095
<i>There's a nice picture of you on the front
page that I'm gonna add to my collection.</i>

253
00:20:06.272 --> 00:20:11.647
<i>Even though we've never met. I feel we have
a lot in common. Nobody understands us.</i>

254
00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:15.948
<i>I'm still wearing a bow tie
so I can look just like you.</i>

255
00:20:16.116 --> 00:20:21.537
<i>After all these letters. I've got good news.
I'm getting out. Isn't that great?</i>

256
00:20:21.705 --> 00:20:24.908
<i>Your number one fan. Junior.</i>

257
00:20:34.010 --> 00:20:36.679
Smoke.

258
00:20:43.019 --> 00:20:44.395
Sir.

259
00:20:45.772 --> 00:20:50.019
Sir. sorry to disturb you
but this letter came for you.

260
00:20:54.657 --> 00:20:57.278
Read this to me.

261
00:20:57.451 --> 00:21:00.073
Hey. it's a letter from JR.

262
00:21:00.246 --> 00:21:04.030
Yeah? Someday
we're gonna meet up on the outside.

263
00:21:04.208 --> 00:21:07.079
We're gonna do some serious damage.

264
00:21:07.253 --> 00:21:09.578
"Good news. I'm getting out."

265
00:21:09.756 --> 00:21:14.881
What? He's getting paroled?
They gotta be out of their minds!

266
00:21:15.053 --> 00:21:17.509
You know that guy?
He's crazier than I am.

267
00:21:17.681 --> 00:21:19.674
Chill. The warden!

268
00:21:20.475 --> 00:21:26.348
Well. well! If it isn't our model prisoner.
looking so pretty today in his little bow tie!

269
00:21:26.523 --> 00:21:28.730
Hey. warden! Catch!

270
00:21:32.697 --> 00:21:36.742
I hope I'm not rushing you.
We can always let nature take its course.

271
00:21:36.909 --> 00:21:40.954
Nature screwed us over.
Let's give commerce a try.

272
00:21:42.832 --> 00:21:48.289
Let's see what I can do. You want a kid
you could love. I'll put you on the waiting list.

273
00:21:48.463 --> 00:21:50.919
You should have a kid in seven years.

274
00:21:51.091 --> 00:21:53.416
- Seven years?
- Unless...

275
00:21:53.594 --> 00:21:58.055
Nah. nah. I didn't say a word.
I did not say a word.

276
00:21:58.224 --> 00:22:01.343
No. what? What were you gonna say?

277
00:22:01.519 --> 00:22:07.106
Well. I really put my foot in my mouth this time
but. I don't know. I like you two.

278
00:22:07.275 --> 00:22:12.270
I like the two of you and when I like
two people. I want to help them out.

279
00:22:12.447 --> 00:22:17.193
That's just my nature.
I want to help out people that I like.

280
00:22:17.369 --> 00:22:21.497
Just this morning
I came upon a seven-year-old.

281
00:22:21.665 --> 00:22:26.826
Smart as a tack. a little rambunctious
but weren't we all at that age?

282
00:22:28.422 --> 00:22:31.293
I think I even have a photo here for you.

283
00:22:32.093 --> 00:22:34.381
He does look presentable in that bow tie.

284
00:22:34.554 --> 00:22:36.262
Adorable!

285
00:22:36.431 --> 00:22:41.306
I don't know. Seven is rather old. I wanted
people to think I had the baby myself.

286
00:22:41.477 --> 00:22:46.021
That's understandable. A lot of women
feel that way. You want a cute little infant.

287
00:22:46.191 --> 00:22:49.145
One that will scream
in the middle of the night

288
00:22:49.319 --> 00:22:54.396
and you'll have to stumble downstairs
in the dark and change his soiled diapers.

289
00:22:54.575 --> 00:22:57.410
You'll do your housework. eat chocolates.

290
00:22:57.578 --> 00:23:01.362
take care of the kid
and you'll put on 50 or 60 pounds.

291
00:23:01.540 --> 00:23:02.572
No diapers?

292
00:23:02.750 --> 00:23:06.084
You like to sleep late.
There'd be no baby waking you up.

293
00:23:06.254 --> 00:23:11.758
We could skip all that baby junk
and move right into the good stuff like...

294
00:23:11.926 --> 00:23:14.548
...parties and more parties!

295
00:23:14.721 --> 00:23:17.046
I could be president of the PTA by September!

296
00:23:17.224 --> 00:23:21.767
- Fuzzball will have someone to play with.
- Yes! Fuzzball's our cat.

297
00:23:21.937 --> 00:23:25.851
I can't believe it! Junior. he loves cats.

298
00:23:26.024 --> 00:23:28.812
Do you hear that? Let's do it.

299
00:23:28.986 --> 00:23:31.821
Mr Peabody. you've got yourself a deal.

300
00:23:31.989 --> 00:23:33.982
And you've got yourself a kid.

301
00:23:41.165 --> 00:23:44.582
Here he comes. Flo. that's our son.

302
00:23:46.630 --> 00:23:49.465
Can you believe it? That's our boy.

303
00:23:49.633 --> 00:23:53.333
He's very handsome.
I'll be the envy of the neighbourhood.

304
00:23:53.512 --> 00:23:56.429
They look like a couple of yahoos.

305
00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:00.841
Hi!

306
00:24:02.146 --> 00:24:03.640
I think I'm gonna cry.

307
00:24:03.814 --> 00:24:06.981
<i>You ever seen a grown man
wear so much blue?</i>

308
00:24:07.151 --> 00:24:09.689
Hey there. little buddy.

309
00:24:09.862 --> 00:24:13.232
I'm Ben. this is Flo. Put it there. partner.

310
00:24:13.408 --> 00:24:16.575
My name's Junior. My favourite
colour's blue. What's yours?

311
00:24:18.163 --> 00:24:21.532
My favourite colour's blue. too.
Can you believe...?

312
00:24:21.708 --> 00:24:25.124
He's perfect. He's wonderful. Come here.

313
00:24:25.295 --> 00:24:28.499
Thank you. sisters. goodbye. Goodbye. kids!

314
00:24:28.674 --> 00:24:31.426
Bye. everybody! Don't forget to write!

315
00:24:38.017 --> 00:24:41.932
We got the pick of the litter.
Everyone's come out to see him off.

316
00:25:02.793 --> 00:25:05.284
Here we are! Isn't this exciting?

317
00:25:05.463 --> 00:25:10.041
Right. everybody out.
This is gonna be so great!

318
00:25:10.218 --> 00:25:16.303
OK. now. everybody over by the house.
This is Junior's first day at his new home.

319
00:25:16.474 --> 00:25:18.882
OK. I want everyone over. Come on.

320
00:25:19.060 --> 00:25:23.105
Junior. put your suitcase down here.
Darling. I want you to hug him.

321
00:25:23.273 --> 00:25:26.358
A lot of teeth. I want everybody to be happy.

322
00:25:26.527 --> 00:25:30.359
- Smile and say. "cheese doodles!"
- Cheese doodles!

323
00:25:30.531 --> 00:25:33.069
That's great. that's terrific.

324
00:25:33.242 --> 00:25:38.153
How come you adopted me?
How come you just didn't have a baby?

325
00:25:38.331 --> 00:25:40.786
Well. gee...

326
00:25:40.958 --> 00:25:45.003
With a baby. you never know
what you're getting. It could be a dud.

327
00:25:45.171 --> 00:25:47.544
But with you there's no surprise.

328
00:25:47.716 --> 00:25:50.503
- Mr Peabody told us how terrific you are.
- He did?

329
00:25:50.677 --> 00:25:55.386
Sure. He said that you were voted
most popular orphan two years in a row.

330
00:25:55.557 --> 00:25:57.846
That was smart of him.

331
00:25:59.311 --> 00:26:04.306
- In we go.
- Wow. This is a great house.

332
00:26:04.483 --> 00:26:07.817
We're going to keep it neat and clean.
aren't we?

333
00:26:13.034 --> 00:26:15.406
I hope you guys are insured.

334
00:26:17.205 --> 00:26:22.081
And you have a cat. Here. kitty-kitty.

335
00:26:22.252 --> 00:26:27.128
No. Junior. make nice with kitty.
Only pet her this way.

336
00:26:27.299 --> 00:26:30.502
I've never seen Fuzzball act like that.

337
00:26:30.678 --> 00:26:33.797
Junior. come here. I want you to meet Polly.

338
00:26:33.973 --> 00:26:38.931
- Polly. say hello to Junior.
- Hello. Hello.

339
00:26:39.103 --> 00:26:41.641
Is that the only word he knows?

340
00:26:41.814 --> 00:26:45.266
- Yes. I want to show you the house.
- Uh-oh!

341
00:26:47.278 --> 00:26:51.228
- Do I get my own bed?
- This is the big time! You get your own room!

342
00:26:51.408 --> 00:26:54.741
- Wow!
- I hope you like clowns.

343
00:26:58.916 --> 00:27:01.323
<i>Oh. my God. They're retarded.</i>

344
00:27:02.336 --> 00:27:04.412
So. what do you think. big guy?

345
00:27:04.588 --> 00:27:08.171
Well. there sure are a lot of clowns.

346
00:27:10.970 --> 00:27:15.928
That must be your new grandpa. You stay
here. We'll give old gramps a big surprise.

347
00:27:16.100 --> 00:27:17.476
Sh!

348
00:27:24.985 --> 00:27:27.024
Dad. are we glad to see you.

349
00:27:27.195 --> 00:27:30.695
What's this big surprise
you dragged me over here for?

350
00:27:30.866 --> 00:27:34.366
Well. Dad. here's a hint.

351
00:27:35.746 --> 00:27:39.032
Oh. my God.

352
00:27:39.208 --> 00:27:41.082
Finally.

353
00:27:41.836 --> 00:27:46.083
You've both cooked up a cute little kid
for my campaign!

354
00:27:46.257 --> 00:27:50.302
I thought you were getting fatter. Mama!
When's my little grandson due?

355
00:27:50.470 --> 00:27:55.013
- Fatter?
- No. Dad. Florence is not gonna have a baby.

356
00:27:55.726 --> 00:27:57.552
You rascal. you!

357
00:27:57.728 --> 00:28:02.805
You followed my advice and took your sperm
to somebody who knows what to do with it.

358
00:28:02.983 --> 00:28:04.228
a surrogate mother.

359
00:28:04.401 --> 00:28:10.487
Tell me something. Do you make out with
a cup or do you get to bump a real live one?

360
00:28:10.658 --> 00:28:12.485
No. Dad. we adopted.

361
00:28:12.660 --> 00:28:15.032
Are you insane?

362
00:28:16.331 --> 00:28:18.738
I thought you'd be happy. Come on.

363
00:28:18.917 --> 00:28:21.871
You don't know
what you're letting yourself in for.

364
00:28:22.045 --> 00:28:24.714
Dopehead mothers. Garbage blood.

365
00:28:24.881 --> 00:28:28.001
His parents may have met in a loony bin.
They might be Democrats.

366
00:28:28.176 --> 00:28:32.969
He's a beautiful kid. Once you meet him.
you'll love him like your very own.

367
00:28:33.140 --> 00:28:37.802
I would like to proudly present the newest
member of the Healy family. Junior!

368
00:28:39.188 --> 00:28:41.062
No! Junior!

369
00:28:41.232 --> 00:28:44.019
That's a thousand-dollar coat!

370
00:28:44.193 --> 00:28:47.479
- Junior. are you in here?
- Junior!

371
00:28:47.655 --> 00:28:51.274
Oh. my God. It's the devil.

372
00:28:51.451 --> 00:28:54.951
- Buddy. are you OK?
- Yeah. just a little smoky.

373
00:28:56.915 --> 00:29:00.995
Look. here's the problem.
This clown must have shorted out.

374
00:29:01.170 --> 00:29:04.669
Sparks were coming out of his nose.
I was so scared.

375
00:29:04.840 --> 00:29:08.459
- Little punk is lying.
- Dad!

376
00:29:08.636 --> 00:29:12.848
I hope you kept the damn receipt.
You got one bad seed there.

377
00:29:13.015 --> 00:29:16.965
He can hear you. You'll hurt his feelings.
It was just an accident.

378
00:29:17.145 --> 00:29:20.846
- Accident! Get rid of him.
- We've made our decision.

379
00:29:21.024 --> 00:29:25.069
OK. but it's the last time
I set foot in this house.

380
00:29:35.247 --> 00:29:37.323
Come on. boys.

381
00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:40.501
- Get back.
- What's happening?

382
00:29:40.670 --> 00:29:43.291
Get rid of that kid!

383
00:29:44.632 --> 00:29:47.966
- Get rid of him.
- Easy!

384
00:29:49.053 --> 00:29:51.805
Get rid of that kid!

385
00:29:57.020 --> 00:30:00.354
Poor Fuzzball. She'll never be the same.

386
00:30:00.524 --> 00:30:02.184
Are you ser...

387
00:30:02.359 --> 00:30:05.859
Is that all you can think of
is your stupid cat?

388
00:30:06.030 --> 00:30:12.033
What about the fact that Father's on his way
to the hospital? Or Junior's traumatic first day?

389
00:30:12.203 --> 00:30:14.279
Did you think about the poor boy?

390
00:30:14.455 --> 00:30:16.448
He must feel horrible.

391
00:30:18.668 --> 00:30:21.289
<i>Yeah. but this might make me feel better.</i>

392
00:30:22.339 --> 00:30:25.957
Fifty. sixty. seventy...

393
00:30:32.683 --> 00:30:34.841
I see a furry bunny.

394
00:30:36.228 --> 00:30:41.603
A furry bunny is running
through delicate white snowflakes.

395
00:30:41.776 --> 00:30:44.397
He's lying. That's not what he sees.

396
00:30:44.570 --> 00:30:48.948
I'm sorry. I'm conducting an examination.
Now what do you see. Martin?

397
00:30:49.117 --> 00:30:51.655
I see a meadow. Pink flowers.

398
00:30:51.828 --> 00:30:57.202
He's lying again. How can he see pink? It's
a black and white picture. There is no pink.

399
00:30:57.375 --> 00:31:00.745
Warden. if you don't stop.
I'll have to ask you to leave.

400
00:31:00.921 --> 00:31:02.830
There is no pink.

401
00:31:05.134 --> 00:31:07.886
I see white fluffy clouds...

402
00:31:08.053 --> 00:31:11.339
No. you don't!
You see murder! You see guts!

403
00:31:11.515 --> 00:31:13.722
I'm going to ask you to leave!

404
00:31:13.893 --> 00:31:17.392
Those damn liberal laws!
Don't you understand? He sees blood!

405
00:31:17.563 --> 00:31:19.640
No. that's what you see.

406
00:31:22.277 --> 00:31:25.064
I am so sorry about that. Martin.

407
00:31:25.989 --> 00:31:29.904
Now. let's get back
to our examination. Shall we?

408
00:31:30.077 --> 00:31:32.034
What do you see in this one?

409
00:31:32.204 --> 00:31:34.777
I see...

410
00:31:34.957 --> 00:31:36.831
...blood!

411
00:31:43.174 --> 00:31:47.172
- Doc. how did it go with the star patient?
- Oh. that guy.

412
00:31:47.345 --> 00:31:50.512
There's a few bricks missing from his building.

413
00:32:21.297 --> 00:32:25.295
- Hey. what are you doing?
- Nothing.

414
00:32:25.468 --> 00:32:26.797
Gosh. what happened here?

415
00:32:26.970 --> 00:32:31.881
I was looking for some paper
to write a get-well note to Big Ben.

416
00:32:32.059 --> 00:32:36.768
That's very thoughtful. Junior.
but these are Mom's private drawers.

417
00:32:36.939 --> 00:32:40.984
You shouldn't go in there. It's where
she keeps her needlepoint and crochet.

418
00:32:52.580 --> 00:32:57.373
I'm really sorry. Mr Healy.
I was scared being all alone in my room.

419
00:32:59.171 --> 00:33:01.294
Of course.

420
00:33:01.465 --> 00:33:06.174
I understand why you're scared.
This is your first night in your new home.

421
00:33:06.345 --> 00:33:09.928
It's gonna take some getting used to. isn't it?

422
00:33:10.099 --> 00:33:16.303
You know. Junior. I'm a little scared myself.
This is my first night being a dad.

423
00:33:16.481 --> 00:33:20.478
- You'll learn quick enough.
- Learn what?

424
00:33:20.652 --> 00:33:24.780
What it's like to be a dad.
Then you'll get rid of me.

425
00:33:25.824 --> 00:33:31.245
Get rid of you? Junior. We're never
gonna get rid of you. You're here forever.

426
00:33:31.413 --> 00:33:34.034
We're gonna do everything together.

427
00:33:34.208 --> 00:33:37.908
We'll ride bikes. go fishing. play catch.

428
00:33:38.087 --> 00:33:41.538
I want to be a good dad.
I want to be a great dad.

429
00:33:41.715 --> 00:33:43.091
You know what?

430
00:33:43.259 --> 00:33:45.750
I will never be too busy to sit down

431
00:33:45.928 --> 00:33:50.674
and listen to what's on my son's mind
over a cup of hot cocoa.

432
00:33:57.274 --> 00:34:01.224
Hey. sleepyhead. Y'all ready to go camping?

433
00:34:01.403 --> 00:34:05.068
I was planning on watching cartoons.

434
00:34:05.240 --> 00:34:07.399
Don't be such a noodle.

435
00:34:07.576 --> 00:34:12.950
When I was your age. your grandfather
was always too busy to take me camping.

436
00:34:13.124 --> 00:34:15.366
You are a lucky duck.

437
00:34:15.543 --> 00:34:18.710
Ben! Bring him.

438
00:34:19.672 --> 00:34:25.462
- Come here. I want you to meet someone.
- Mrs Henderson! And little Miss Lucy!

439
00:34:25.637 --> 00:34:27.713
What a nice surprise!

440
00:34:27.889 --> 00:34:33.975
We heard about your little accident and
we thought this fruitcake might cheer you up.

441
00:34:34.855 --> 00:34:37.013
Thank you!

442
00:34:37.191 --> 00:34:40.607
I would like you to meet my son Junior.

443
00:34:40.778 --> 00:34:43.862
- Pleased to meet you. ladies.
- Oh. my!

444
00:34:44.031 --> 00:34:47.235
He's a perfect little gentleman. Isn't he. Lucy?

445
00:34:47.410 --> 00:34:49.237
He's so big.

446
00:34:49.412 --> 00:34:53.789
Yesterday they didn't even have a kid
and now they have a seven-year-old.

447
00:34:53.958 --> 00:34:56.331
That's gross.

448
00:34:56.503 --> 00:35:00.631
- I don't want him at my party.
- Lucy.

449
00:35:00.799 --> 00:35:06.469
But. Mother. he dresses like the man
that cremated Uncle Leo.

450
00:35:06.638 --> 00:35:09.176
Lucy's turning six this week

451
00:35:09.350 --> 00:35:13.810
but I don't think we'll have a clown this year.

452
00:35:13.979 --> 00:35:17.514
Or balloons. Or ice cream.

453
00:35:19.777 --> 00:35:26.030
I'm having a birthday party Saturday.
I think it would be nice if you came.

454
00:35:30.247 --> 00:35:34.743
We'll see you Saturday at two.
Come on. Lucy. get in the car.

455
00:35:34.918 --> 00:35:39.794
- Thanks. I'll return the lovely platter.
- Thanks again.

456
00:35:39.965 --> 00:35:43.797
We have finally been accepted.
This parent crap is really paying off.

457
00:35:43.969 --> 00:35:48.382
It's a dream come true. A birthday party.
Now we're going camping with our son.

458
00:35:48.558 --> 00:35:52.935
Not me. I'm going to buy a dress
for the party. Give me some money.

459
00:35:53.104 --> 00:35:56.853
- You're not going camping with us?
- Not on your life.

460
00:35:57.025 --> 00:35:59.267
OK.

461
00:35:59.444 --> 00:36:01.271
Junior! This gives me an idea.

462
00:36:01.446 --> 00:36:06.073
I don't see why my son
shouldn't be getting his own allowance.

463
00:36:06.243 --> 00:36:08.568
- What do you say?
- All right!

464
00:36:08.746 --> 00:36:13.455
This is gonna give you a good opportunity
to learn to manage money.

465
00:36:14.460 --> 00:36:16.666
How do you manage a buck?

466
00:36:16.837 --> 00:36:21.500
Come on. Mr Molasses. let's go. We're late.

467
00:36:29.392 --> 00:36:32.393
Neat! Bears!

468
00:36:32.562 --> 00:36:36.809
Don't worry. buddy.
bears rarely attack unless provoked.

469
00:36:36.984 --> 00:36:40.519
Let's keep our eyes peeled for camp site 32.

470
00:36:40.696 --> 00:36:42.772
That's the one Roy reserved especially for us.

471
00:36:44.950 --> 00:36:49.577
Nice spot your friend reserved
especially for us. Mr Healy

472
00:36:49.747 --> 00:36:54.623
- This is nature. huh? The sky. the trees?
- The toilets.

473
00:36:54.794 --> 00:37:00.584
You're not gonna see the sunset over there.
Come on over. watch on our river-bank.

474
00:37:00.759 --> 00:37:03.001
I'd tell him to shove it. Mr Healy.

475
00:37:03.178 --> 00:37:08.136
It's no big deal. More important.
why don't you call me Dad? I'd really like that.

476
00:37:08.308 --> 00:37:11.428
I want to go home and watch TV.

477
00:37:11.603 --> 00:37:14.059
TV? What's TV compared to the...

478
00:37:14.231 --> 00:37:17.149
...to the call of the wild bobolink.
and that spruce?

479
00:37:19.987 --> 00:37:22.313
That's a pretty big bobolink.

480
00:37:22.490 --> 00:37:28.077
<i>Old MacDonald had a farm
E- i-e-i-o...</i>

481
00:37:29.372 --> 00:37:32.290
Hey. Little Ben.

482
00:37:33.752 --> 00:37:37.002
- Kids. the wienies are almost done!
- Yeah!

483
00:37:37.172 --> 00:37:39.461
I don't believe this.

484
00:37:39.633 --> 00:37:45.257
<i>Those are Roy's kids. They're sharing a brain.
The one on the end has it today.</i>

485
00:37:47.600 --> 00:37:51.645
Little Ben. Come here. inside.
Get in here. come on.

486
00:37:53.815 --> 00:37:58.940
- How does it feel. camping with your son?
- Roy. it's great. It's a dream come true.

487
00:37:59.112 --> 00:38:03.489
Forget the fact that you had to go
to the kid emporium and buy one.

488
00:38:03.658 --> 00:38:07.407
We can't all produce six perfect little angels
like me and Harriet.

489
00:38:07.579 --> 00:38:10.746
I only got one. but he's one in a million.

490
00:38:13.502 --> 00:38:15.459
Gee. Roy.

491
00:38:15.629 --> 00:38:19.129
- It's gonna give the kids a scare. isn't it?
- You got me.

492
00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:24.342
- Wait a minute. I got something else for you.
- I can't wait to see their faces light up.

493
00:38:24.514 --> 00:38:26.388
It's so real.

494
00:38:26.558 --> 00:38:30.805
Little Ben. now that you're a father.
try this on for size.

495
00:38:35.859 --> 00:38:38.148
Gee. thanks. Roy.

496
00:38:38.987 --> 00:38:43.531
<i>The monkey thought it was all in fun
Pop goes the weasell</i>

497
00:38:43.701 --> 00:38:48.529
<i>A penny for a spool of thread
A penny for a needle</i>

498
00:38:48.706 --> 00:38:52.870
<i>That's the way the money goes
Pop goes the weasell</i>

499
00:38:53.044 --> 00:38:56.579
- All right! What do we do now?
- Let's tell ghost stories.

500
00:38:56.756 --> 00:38:59.757
- Let's roast marshmallows.
- Let's light a forest fire.

501
00:38:59.926 --> 00:39:04.635
- Don't you know it's bad to light forest fires?
- That's the whole point.

502
00:39:04.806 --> 00:39:08.721
- I'm gonna tell my daddy on you!
- I'm gonna tell.

503
00:39:08.894 --> 00:39:11.848
- Give him the silent treatment.
- Yeah. ignore him.

504
00:39:14.608 --> 00:39:17.894
Ignore this.

505
00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:20.146
Gross!

506
00:39:24.786 --> 00:39:29.531
This outdoor life is gonna be just the ticket
for Junior. He's gonna blossom out here.

507
00:39:29.707 --> 00:39:31.831
We sure do enjoy it.

508
00:39:32.002 --> 00:39:36.296
I bet you've never been camping before.
It's so much fun.

509
00:39:36.465 --> 00:39:39.668
There's singing. Marshmallows.

510
00:39:39.843 --> 00:39:42.630
And all sorts of stupid humans to scare.

511
00:39:45.599 --> 00:39:50.096
<i>Row. row. row your boat
Gently down the stream</i>

512
00:39:50.271 --> 00:39:54.483
<i>Merrily. merrily. merrily. merrily
Life is but a dream</i>

513
00:40:04.619 --> 00:40:06.695
Roy. you devil.

514
00:40:10.459 --> 00:40:15.702
What's the matter. kids? You afraid
of a measly little bear? He's not so bad.

515
00:40:16.715 --> 00:40:20.049
Great. This is great. Roy.

516
00:40:21.512 --> 00:40:25.095
Let's see if he's ticklish.
Mr Bear ticklish? Coochie-coochie!

517
00:40:26.517 --> 00:40:27.893
Coochie...

518
00:40:28.061 --> 00:40:31.346
That was close! You...

519
00:40:33.942 --> 00:40:35.317
Roy?

520
00:40:35.485 --> 00:40:38.059
Roy! Help!

521
00:40:38.238 --> 00:40:40.646
Help! Help!

522
00:40:51.335 --> 00:40:54.005
Stay here. stay here.

523
00:40:55.506 --> 00:40:57.879
- Where did he go?
- I think it left.

524
00:41:20.699 --> 00:41:24.151
He must have learned it from the tourists.

525
00:41:42.306 --> 00:41:44.133
Roy!

526
00:41:50.231 --> 00:41:54.727
I can't get it out of my head that
Junior was responsible for the camping thing.

527
00:41:54.902 --> 00:41:57.191
He was laughing his head off.

528
00:41:57.363 --> 00:41:59.403
Just lock him in his room tonight.

529
00:41:59.574 --> 00:42:03.275
It says that children often misbehave
just to get attention

530
00:42:03.453 --> 00:42:08.411
and we should resort to discipline only when
other forms of positive reinforcement fail.

531
00:42:09.960 --> 00:42:12.202
Up yours! Up yours!

532
00:42:12.379 --> 00:42:15.879
- Reinforce that.
- Dickhead.

533
00:42:21.222 --> 00:42:24.507
Mrs Henderson. your home is lovely.

534
00:42:24.684 --> 00:42:28.017
- Call me Marion.
- Marion. this is fabulous.

535
00:42:28.187 --> 00:42:32.933
There's nothing more wonderful than
children playing. hearing them laughing.

536
00:42:33.109 --> 00:42:36.443
- Excuse me.
- Did you see Junior's outfit?

537
00:42:37.239 --> 00:42:39.943
Isn't he precious?

538
00:42:45.706 --> 00:42:48.660
Also. Big Ben means big business!

539
00:42:48.834 --> 00:42:53.081
Junior. I got some buttons for the kids
and some stickers for their bikes.

540
00:42:53.255 --> 00:42:57.205
Do your grandfather a favour
and pass them out among your friends.

541
00:42:57.385 --> 00:43:00.090
What for?

542
00:43:00.263 --> 00:43:02.137
What for?

543
00:43:02.307 --> 00:43:06.387
- For ten bucks. that's what's for.
- Sure. Grandpa!

544
00:43:06.561 --> 00:43:08.353
Kids. huh?

545
00:43:22.078 --> 00:43:25.577
Put that down! That's mine!
These are all my presents!

546
00:43:25.748 --> 00:43:31.039
- I was only looking at it.
- You're gonna break it! Get away from it!

547
00:43:31.212 --> 00:43:36.005
- Who's that?
- He can't play with us. He's got cooties.

548
00:43:36.176 --> 00:43:39.093
He's not even a real kid. He's adopted.

549
00:43:39.262 --> 00:43:41.800
Gross!

550
00:43:41.973 --> 00:43:46.018
All right. boys and girls. come on out.
Time for the magic show.

551
00:43:46.186 --> 00:43:47.645
All right!

552
00:43:49.690 --> 00:43:52.062
- You can't come out.
- Why not?

553
00:43:52.234 --> 00:43:53.515
'Cause I said so.

554
00:43:53.694 --> 00:43:59.151
It's my party and I get to say who
can watch my magic show and who can't.

555
00:44:15.384 --> 00:44:19.002
- Why aren't you outside?
- Clowns are dumb.

556
00:44:19.179 --> 00:44:21.421
It's tough being left out. isn't it?

557
00:44:25.478 --> 00:44:29.476
If I give you something.
would you promise to take care of it?

558
00:44:37.407 --> 00:44:41.025
My grandfather gave this to me
just before he died.

559
00:44:41.203 --> 00:44:43.872
What is it?

560
00:44:44.039 --> 00:44:48.167
It's a prune. hardened. It's a hardened prune.

561
00:44:48.335 --> 00:44:53.330
Grandfather became a little senile toward
the end. He thought it resembled Roosevelt.

562
00:44:53.507 --> 00:44:59.213
But the important thing
is that it's a bond between two people.

563
00:45:00.973 --> 00:45:03.595
I've kept it in my pocket for 30 years.

564
00:45:03.768 --> 00:45:07.386
- Ben. I want you to meet the Hofsteders!
- Coming. sweetheart.

565
00:45:08.356 --> 00:45:11.772
- I know you'll take good care of it.
- Ben. move it!

566
00:45:20.160 --> 00:45:23.612
<i>You can't come to my magic show.</i>

567
00:45:24.373 --> 00:45:26.911
<i>I had some magic of my own.</i>

568
00:45:27.877 --> 00:45:31.495
<i>It's my party and I'll cry if I want to</i>

569
00:45:31.673 --> 00:45:36.002
<i>Cry if I want to
Cry if I want to</i>

570
00:45:36.177 --> 00:45:41.516
<i>You would cry too if it happened to you</i>

571
00:45:42.976 --> 00:45:46.760
<i>Nobody knows where my Johnny has gone</i>

572
00:45:46.939 --> 00:45:50.639
<i>But Judy left the same time</i>

573
00:45:50.818 --> 00:45:56.856
<i>Why was he holding her hand?
When he's supposed to be mine</i>

574
00:45:58.200 --> 00:46:01.617
<i>It's my party and I'll cry if I want to</i>

575
00:46:01.788 --> 00:46:05.702
<i>Cry if I want to
Cry if I want to</i>

576
00:46:05.875 --> 00:46:10.668
<i>You would cry too if it happened to you</i>

577
00:46:13.049 --> 00:46:16.501
<i>Play all my records
Keep dancing all night</i>

578
00:46:16.678 --> 00:46:20.759
<i>But we were alone for a while</i>

579
00:46:20.933 --> 00:46:27.386
<i>Till Johnny's dancing with me
I've got no reason to smile</i>

580
00:46:27.565 --> 00:46:30.815
<i>It's my party and I'll cry if I want to</i>

581
00:46:30.985 --> 00:46:34.983
<i>Cry if I want to
Cry if I want to</i>

582
00:46:35.156 --> 00:46:39.783
<i>You would cry too if it happened to you...</i>

583
00:46:57.555 --> 00:47:01.138
<i>Judy and Johnny
Just walked through the door</i>

584
00:47:01.309 --> 00:47:04.974
<i>Like a queen with her king</i>

585
00:47:05.146 --> 00:47:12.027
<i>Oh. what a birthday surprise
Judy's wearing his ring</i>

586
00:47:12.195 --> 00:47:15.529
<i>It's my party and I'll cry if I want to</i>

587
00:47:15.699 --> 00:47:19.150
<i>Cry if I want to
Cry if I want to</i>

588
00:47:19.328 --> 00:47:25.247
<i>You would cry too if it happened to you</i>

589
00:47:25.417 --> 00:47:30.210
<i>Oh-oh. it's my party and I'll cry if I want to</i>

590
00:47:30.381 --> 00:47:34.130
<i>Cry if I want to
Cry if I want to</i>

591
00:47:34.302 --> 00:47:40.222
<i>You would cry too if it happened to you</i>

592
00:47:41.309 --> 00:47:45.639
<i>Perhaps this was the one step too far.
This could be a problem.</i>

593
00:47:45.814 --> 00:47:48.435
- I think we've got a problem.
- You think so?

594
00:47:48.609 --> 00:47:52.357
We should get rid of the kid
and buy a new cat!

595
00:47:52.529 --> 00:47:57.986
- You're not making any sense.
- Wanna make sense? Show him who's boss!

596
00:47:58.160 --> 00:48:00.486
Here. be a man.

597
00:48:06.169 --> 00:48:11.246
Please. God. I'm so sorry for what I've done.
I won't ever do it again. I promise.

598
00:48:11.424 --> 00:48:15.125
And I don't ever
want to cause Mr Healy any trouble.

599
00:48:15.303 --> 00:48:18.470
He's the only one that's ever been nice to me.

600
00:48:21.226 --> 00:48:23.599
Please don't spank me. Mr Healy.

601
00:48:24.897 --> 00:48:28.515
I don't want to
but you're gonna have to be punished.

602
00:48:28.693 --> 00:48:32.192
So. I'm gonna take back your allowance.

603
00:48:32.363 --> 00:48:34.237
The whole buck?

604
00:48:34.407 --> 00:48:37.278
That's right. Now. just hand it over.

605
00:48:44.209 --> 00:48:46.665
<i>I wonder if he's got change for a 20.</i>

606
00:48:53.510 --> 00:48:55.254
OK.

607
00:48:55.429 --> 00:48:57.885
I think you'd better go right to bed.

608
00:48:58.057 --> 00:49:03.217
Just use this time to think about
what you've done and what you're going to do.

609
00:49:03.396 --> 00:49:06.148
Understand?

610
00:49:08.484 --> 00:49:11.236
I hope you've learned a lesson.

611
00:49:11.404 --> 00:49:14.358
Goodnight.

612
00:49:14.533 --> 00:49:17.949
<i>What is this guy. nice or something?</i>

613
00:49:30.591 --> 00:49:33.711
- Can I help you?
- Fill her up.

614
00:49:39.350 --> 00:49:42.055
Smiley pies!

615
00:49:42.228 --> 00:49:45.183
I ain't had a smiley pie in 15 years.

616
00:50:20.102 --> 00:50:24.598
<i>Now. Cold River's favourite son.
Big Ben Healyl</i>

617
00:50:26.775 --> 00:50:31.521
First of all. I'd like to thank everyone
who supported me in my race for Mayor.

618
00:50:33.991 --> 00:50:35.818
This is the Founders Day game.

619
00:50:35.993 --> 00:50:40.572
It doesn't matter who wins or loses.
just so long as Big Ben wins for Mayor.

620
00:50:42.459 --> 00:50:48.378
When you hit one out and that scoreboard
lights up. I want you to remember Big Ben.

621
00:50:58.350 --> 00:51:01.020
<i>We go to the seventh inning tied.</i>

622
00:51:14.618 --> 00:51:20.870
All right. somebody's gonna have to pinch-hit
for Andy. OK. buddy. this is your big moment.

623
00:51:21.708 --> 00:51:25.872
- Who. me?
- Of course you. Junior. I need you to bat.

624
00:51:26.046 --> 00:51:30.590
Get up. grab a helmet.
Get a bat. that's a boy.

625
00:51:30.760 --> 00:51:34.176
But I don't know how to play baseball.

626
00:51:34.347 --> 00:51:37.134
Now is as good a time as any to learn.

627
00:51:37.308 --> 00:51:40.760
- But what happens if...
- It doesn't matter what happens.

628
00:51:40.937 --> 00:51:45.065
The important thing is that you stand up there
and take your cuts. OK?

629
00:51:45.233 --> 00:51:48.151
I'll be proud of you no matter how you do.

630
00:51:48.320 --> 00:51:53.990
Are you out of your mind. putting that
little monster in the game? I'm on a campaign.

631
00:51:54.159 --> 00:51:57.279
Junior'll do just fine. Dad.
You can do it. buddy.

632
00:51:57.454 --> 00:52:02.282
Nice little tie. moose breath. Bet you sell
a lot of Girl Scout cookies wearing that.

633
00:52:02.460 --> 00:52:04.536
No batter. Cort.

634
00:52:04.712 --> 00:52:07.286
He's cute. isn't he?

635
00:52:11.261 --> 00:52:13.716
Strike one.

636
00:52:14.472 --> 00:52:19.051
If that kid wasn't adopted.
I'd swear he was your real son.

637
00:52:19.227 --> 00:52:22.679
You weren't on the team
the last time we beat you.

638
00:52:22.856 --> 00:52:25.347
The guy I'm staying with is the coach.

639
00:52:25.526 --> 00:52:28.942
You mean that big dork
who buys everyone ice cream.

640
00:52:29.113 --> 00:52:31.189
He is not a dork!

641
00:52:31.365 --> 00:52:35.612
Watch the pitcher. not the catcher.
buddy. come on!

642
00:52:47.799 --> 00:52:50.670
My new car! Oh. my God!

643
00:52:50.844 --> 00:52:56.550
Shake it off. Tighten up that grip. all right?
Meet the ball. Hold onto the bat. OK?

644
00:52:56.725 --> 00:52:59.263
- Come on. boy!
- Good idea.

645
00:52:59.436 --> 00:53:02.058
Yeah. hold on to the bat.

646
00:53:02.231 --> 00:53:05.066
Son of dork. son of dork!

647
00:53:05.318 --> 00:53:09.398
Son of dork!

648
00:53:10.406 --> 00:53:12.732
Oh. no.

649
00:53:25.881 --> 00:53:28.039
Drop the bat. son!

650
00:53:32.179 --> 00:53:34.089
That's no good!

651
00:53:34.265 --> 00:53:36.423
You can't do that.

652
00:53:36.601 --> 00:53:39.139
Whoa!

653
00:53:40.438 --> 00:53:43.772
Drop the bat. Junior! Are you nuts?

654
00:53:47.529 --> 00:53:49.771
Whoa!

655
00:54:00.834 --> 00:54:02.911
Come on. I got something for you!

656
00:54:06.716 --> 00:54:08.673
Ow!

657
00:54:09.469 --> 00:54:12.304
Touchdown! Touchdown! Touchdown!

658
00:54:12.472 --> 00:54:15.592
Touchdown!

659
00:54:26.945 --> 00:54:29.104
We've adopted Satan.

660
00:54:29.281 --> 00:54:33.149
I don't now what you could've been
thinking about! We've done all we can.

661
00:54:33.327 --> 00:54:37.159
Now. you wait right here.
I'm gonna get the priest.

662
00:54:39.751 --> 00:54:43.831
Hello. Mr Healy. Remember me?
You sold me a canteen.

663
00:54:44.005 --> 00:54:46.543
Boy. did we have a great camping trip!

664
00:54:46.716 --> 00:54:49.966
I caught three fish. My dad was really proud.

665
00:54:50.136 --> 00:54:52.509
Blow it out your ass.

666
00:54:55.058 --> 00:54:57.514
Junior. Junior!

667
00:54:57.686 --> 00:54:59.762
Get back here. you little heathen!

668
00:55:01.148 --> 00:55:04.268
Junior! Where are you. you little creep?

669
00:55:22.003 --> 00:55:25.538
Bless me. Father. for I have sinned.
Father? Father?

670
00:55:27.468 --> 00:55:30.919
Father. I'm at the end of my rope.
It's about my kid.

671
00:55:31.096 --> 00:55:36.850
He's a real problem. He does terrible things.
My father hates him. My wife hates him.

672
00:55:37.019 --> 00:55:38.811
Everybody hates him.

673
00:55:38.980 --> 00:55:41.435
Everybody except me. And I've had it.

674
00:55:41.607 --> 00:55:44.692
God! I've failed. Father. The kid hates me.

675
00:55:44.861 --> 00:55:49.986
It's time I faced up to what I do have to do.
I'm gonna take him back to the orphanage.

676
00:55:50.158 --> 00:55:54.701
No. no. you don't want to do that!
That's the worst thing you could do!

677
00:56:08.761 --> 00:56:11.798
- Can I call you back?
- He's all yours.

678
00:56:11.973 --> 00:56:14.725
- Can we discuss this?
- There is nothing to discuss.

679
00:56:14.893 --> 00:56:19.353
- We're signing him back over to you now!
- Bad parents make bad children!

680
00:56:19.522 --> 00:56:21.978
I'm a bad parent because I hate my kid?

681
00:56:22.150 --> 00:56:25.769
- There is something strange about that boy!
- He is twisted!

682
00:56:25.946 --> 00:56:29.232
- You took him! He's yours!
- You conned us into it!

683
00:56:29.408 --> 00:56:34.782
What am I supposed to do with the little
creep? He's already been returned 30 times!

684
00:56:34.955 --> 00:56:37.162
This makes 31!

685
00:56:37.333 --> 00:56:40.038
"We don't care
about brown hair and brown eyes."

686
00:56:40.211 --> 00:56:43.794
"We want to take him into our home
and let him play with our cat!"

687
00:56:43.965 --> 00:56:46.456
Hold it! Stop. wait!

688
00:56:46.634 --> 00:56:50.466
What are we talking about?
Thirty? Thirty times?

689
00:56:50.639 --> 00:56:53.130
Flo. did you hear that?

690
00:56:53.308 --> 00:56:55.930
This is a human being we're talking about!

691
00:56:56.103 --> 00:56:58.475
That kid's a monster!

692
00:56:58.647 --> 00:57:02.597
Flo. we're doing what everybody else
has done to this child.

693
00:57:02.776 --> 00:57:06.192
- It's easy to give up on a kid.
- Damn straight it is.

694
00:57:06.363 --> 00:57:11.702
Isn't that what's wrong with the world today?
Everybody's looking for the easy way out.

695
00:57:11.869 --> 00:57:16.911
They're hoping that
their problems will just go away.

696
00:57:17.083 --> 00:57:21.247
But problems don't just go. Flo. you know?

697
00:57:21.421 --> 00:57:26.130
So. the question before us is what are
we gonna do with our little problem child?

698
00:57:26.301 --> 00:57:28.508
I'll tell you.

699
00:57:28.679 --> 00:57:33.886
Something that no one's ever done
for him before. We're gonna love him. Flo.

700
00:57:35.019 --> 00:57:39.432
We're gonna love him when he's bad.
we're gonna love him when he's worse.

701
00:57:39.607 --> 00:57:43.771
until one day he's gonna crack and say.

702
00:57:43.945 --> 00:57:48.192
"Hey. these folks really do love me."

703
00:57:48.366 --> 00:57:50.738
"They ain't gonna quit on me."

704
00:57:50.910 --> 00:57:53.995
"I don't have to be bad any more."

705
00:57:54.164 --> 00:57:58.244
"What the hay!
I can be president of the United States!"

706
00:57:58.919 --> 00:58:04.459
President? Are you brain damaged? Junior's
gonna be a convict before he's in third grade!

707
00:58:04.633 --> 00:58:06.176
Sh!

708
00:58:06.343 --> 00:58:08.669
Junior? Son?

709
00:58:10.139 --> 00:58:13.639
- Unlock the door.
- You said you were gonna keep me forever.

710
00:58:15.019 --> 00:58:18.223
I am. I'm sorry. I just made a mistake.

711
00:58:18.398 --> 00:58:22.147
Trust me. We're not gonna
take you back to the orphanage.

712
00:58:22.319 --> 00:58:27.526
I don't believe you! You only pretended
to be my friend. You're just like all the others.

713
00:58:29.243 --> 00:58:32.409
Junior? Now. come on. son.

714
00:58:34.039 --> 00:58:36.791
You moron. You left the keys in the car.

715
00:58:37.877 --> 00:58:41.625
Hey. he can drive! Boy. that's great!

716
00:58:42.340 --> 00:58:46.385
Look at you handle this baby!
I'm so proud of you. son!

717
00:58:47.679 --> 00:58:49.553
Junior!

718
00:58:49.722 --> 00:58:52.677
Hold it!

719
00:58:53.852 --> 00:58:55.595
Get out of the way!

720
00:58:56.271 --> 00:58:58.347
Left! Turn left!

721
00:58:59.316 --> 00:59:02.151
Right. Junior.

722
00:59:05.155 --> 00:59:09.070
No!

723
00:59:09.243 --> 00:59:11.615
No. don't touch that!

724
00:59:13.539 --> 00:59:15.865
Junior!

725
00:59:27.262 --> 00:59:29.089
Watch out!

726
00:59:35.771 --> 00:59:39.354
<i>Born to be wild</i>

727
01:00:03.342 --> 01:00:04.717
Hello?

728
01:00:05.469 --> 01:00:07.925
Ben? Jim O'Connor.
Are you sitting down?

729
01:00:08.097 --> 01:00:09.472
Yes.

730
01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:14.765
Bad news. Your father cleaned out your bank
account to pay for the damage to his store.

731
01:00:14.937 --> 01:00:18.271
Nothing can make up
for the loss of your life savings...

732
01:00:18.441 --> 01:00:19.816
Ben?

733
01:00:31.163 --> 01:00:33.239
<i>Uh-ohl He's lost it nowl</i>

734
01:00:47.930 --> 01:00:50.256
All right!

735
01:00:54.938 --> 01:00:57.263
Private business.

736
01:00:57.440 --> 01:00:59.149
Hi!

737
01:00:59.317 --> 01:01:04.692
- Get out of my way. kid. I'm looking for JR.
- That's me! Junior!

738
01:01:08.536 --> 01:01:11.821
I don't have time for this crap. kid.

739
01:01:11.998 --> 01:01:16.956
Now. the guy I'm looking for is an ex-con
and he's as mean as a rattlesnake.

740
01:01:17.128 --> 01:01:20.331
That's me. dummy! I sent you all those letters.

741
01:01:20.506 --> 01:01:26.343
Man. I drove a thousand miles
to hang out with a seven-year-old?

742
01:01:26.513 --> 01:01:30.345
- I'm gonna be eight in two weeks.
- Don't count on it.

743
01:01:34.855 --> 01:01:40.360
Mr Healy. Mrs Healy. I'd like you to meet
the greatest guy in the whole wide world.

744
01:01:40.528 --> 01:01:42.236
Martin...

745
01:01:43.864 --> 01:01:45.738
Uncle Marty!

746
01:01:45.908 --> 01:01:48.316
Marty. this is Mr and Mrs Healy

747
01:01:48.494 --> 01:01:52.492
and that's the $3.000 stereo system
and the console TV.

748
01:01:52.665 --> 01:01:54.623
How wonderful. an uncle!

749
01:01:54.793 --> 01:01:57.248
You absolutely must stay the night.

750
01:01:57.420 --> 01:02:01.039
It is so wonderful to meet
the uncle of darling little Junior.

751
01:02:01.216 --> 01:02:05.843
Did you hear that? Uncle Marty.
We've gotta treat this guy like royalty.

752
01:02:06.013 --> 01:02:11.304
We've gotta make him think Junior's an angel.
He'll leave and take the little brat with him.

753
01:02:11.477 --> 01:02:14.312
Everybody just loves Junior.

754
01:02:14.480 --> 01:02:19.356
For pocket money he helps some
of the older residents with their groceries.

755
01:02:19.527 --> 01:02:21.401
Isn't that right. Ben?

756
01:02:23.615 --> 01:02:29.819
If only he had a blood relative taking care of
him. someone with a natural tie. Like an uncle!

757
01:02:29.996 --> 01:02:32.155
- More meatloaf?
- Yeah.

758
01:02:32.332 --> 01:02:34.325
I'll get you some.

759
01:02:34.501 --> 01:02:37.455
<i>This guy is just so appealing.</i>

760
01:02:37.629 --> 01:02:40.037
I'll give you a hand.

761
01:02:42.802 --> 01:02:48.176
Your nephew is such a delight. He's always
cleaning and tidying up after all of us.

762
01:02:48.349 --> 01:02:50.805
Perfect for a single man living alone.

763
01:02:50.977 --> 01:02:53.053
Are you a bachelor. Marty?

764
01:02:55.482 --> 01:02:58.732
I ain't been with a woman in 15 years.

765
01:02:58.902 --> 01:03:01.773
Women just love single male parents.

766
01:03:01.947 --> 01:03:06.656
If you had a kid like Junior
the women would be flocking over you.

767
01:03:16.879 --> 01:03:19.501
Did you say 15 years?

768
01:03:21.217 --> 01:03:23.293
Wait.

769
01:03:26.556 --> 01:03:29.759
Stop it!

770
01:04:01.843 --> 01:04:04.631
Look at all the stuff I brought for our trip.

771
01:04:04.805 --> 01:04:10.511
I got my ammo. There's guns.
hand grenades and even dynamite.

772
01:04:13.856 --> 01:04:19.859
These are toys. What are you
jerking me around for? This is kiddies' stuff!

773
01:04:22.323 --> 01:04:26.107
What did you do that for?
Don't we need supplies?

774
01:04:26.286 --> 01:04:29.038
What? I'm not working with you!

775
01:04:29.789 --> 01:04:34.333
But I thought we were gonna be partners.
I thought you liked me.

776
01:04:34.503 --> 01:04:38.121
I don't like no one. I work alone.

777
01:04:41.218 --> 01:04:46.343
Goodbye. Junior! Goodbye. Flo!
Oh. I am so sad to see you go.

778
01:04:46.515 --> 01:04:50.300
A hundred thousand dollars?
You can keep 'em!

779
01:04:50.478 --> 01:04:53.681
Good morning! Hello. sunshine!

780
01:04:55.733 --> 01:04:58.059
This was supposed to be our honeymoon!

781
01:04:58.236 --> 01:05:01.771
You said you loved me!
You called me a little kumquat.

782
01:05:01.948 --> 01:05:04.653
This is our honeymoon. you moron!

783
01:05:04.826 --> 01:05:07.448
Moron? Moron?

784
01:05:07.621 --> 01:05:12.497
I went to Radcliffe! I'm not a bimbo
you can tie up and do what you want with!

785
01:05:12.668 --> 01:05:14.744
- You shut up!
- I will not!

786
01:05:14.920 --> 01:05:20.081
Let me out of here! You stupid piece of...
You're gonna regret this!

787
01:05:20.259 --> 01:05:25.420
I'm gonna be waiting and when I'm done
with you you're gonna be singing falsetto!

788
01:05:25.598 --> 01:05:29.430
He-e-e-ere's Daddy!

789
01:05:32.189 --> 01:05:34.680
Goodbye. Junior!

790
01:05:34.858 --> 01:05:38.061
<i>Adiosl Hasta luegol</i>

791
01:05:39.279 --> 01:05:41.319
Sayonara!

792
01:05:42.366 --> 01:05:44.691
Yeah!

793
01:05:45.953 --> 01:05:48.824
Yes. that's very creative. Junior.

794
01:05:48.998 --> 01:05:51.750
Yeah. right on the money.

795
01:06:12.022 --> 01:06:14.560
He liked me.

796
01:06:14.733 --> 01:06:17.853
All this time he actually liked me.

797
01:06:30.166 --> 01:06:33.500
Vote for Big Ben. Here. read this.

798
01:06:36.548 --> 01:06:41.294
You can't go in. Your father's making
a television appearance for his campaign.

799
01:06:42.888 --> 01:06:45.214
Dad. I gotta talk to you!

800
01:06:45.391 --> 01:06:50.730
- What are you doing? I'm about to go on air!
- Florence and Junior have been kidnapped.

801
01:06:50.897 --> 01:06:52.307
Five minutes.

802
01:06:52.482 --> 01:06:54.937
- I need $100.000.
- Are you insane?

803
01:06:55.109 --> 01:07:00.614
That kid is a monster and your wife is
the original pain in the ass. It's for the best.

804
01:07:00.782 --> 01:07:04.400
- Are you gonna lend me the money?
- No. I'm not.

805
01:07:04.578 --> 01:07:08.410
You work for me. I know what you get.
You're a credit risk.

806
01:07:10.292 --> 01:07:12.368
Then I quit as your son!

807
01:07:12.544 --> 01:07:16.377
Just get out of here.
I got a goddamn campaign to win.

808
01:07:16.549 --> 01:07:20.796
Your campaign.
the one thing you do care about.

809
01:07:21.929 --> 01:07:26.508
Why don't you tell the voters
what you really plan on doing with this town?

810
01:07:26.684 --> 01:07:28.760
I don't give a rat's ass for the voters.

811
01:07:28.937 --> 01:07:33.480
<i>- We're ready with that live feed.
- All I care about is power and money.</i>

812
01:07:34.276 --> 01:07:38.570
<i>America for the Americansl
You believe that nonsense?</i>

813
01:07:38.739 --> 01:07:42.238
<i>I'd sell my soul to the Japanese
if they'd make me an offer.</i>

814
01:07:42.409 --> 01:07:45.660
<i>Don't come sucking round me
if you want something.</i>

815
01:07:45.830 --> 01:07:48.403
<i>The only thing you'll get from me is this.</i>

816
01:08:07.686 --> 01:08:09.928
- Hello?
- You got the money?

817
01:08:10.731 --> 01:08:12.106
Yeah.

818
01:08:12.274 --> 01:08:15.560
Good. Bring it to the circus.

819
01:08:15.736 --> 01:08:18.607
I'll be waiting at the tiger cage.

820
01:08:20.992 --> 01:08:23.447
Roy! I need your car.

821
01:08:23.619 --> 01:08:26.656
- Forget it. We're going hunting.
- So am I.

822
01:08:26.831 --> 01:08:31.707
You can't borrow it. We're all packed up
and ready to go. What are you doing?

823
01:08:31.878 --> 01:08:33.954
You're not going anywhere. buddy.

824
01:08:36.007 --> 01:08:37.668
Wait a minute.

825
01:08:37.843 --> 01:08:40.168
Great. the joke's over. Come on back.

826
01:08:40.345 --> 01:08:42.421
What do you think you're doing?

827
01:08:47.144 --> 01:08:49.552
Hey! Hey. get back here. you!

828
01:08:52.942 --> 01:08:55.231
- What is he doing?
- Get back here!

829
01:08:56.988 --> 01:08:59.693
Gee. I've never been to the circus before.

830
01:08:59.866 --> 01:09:03.531
- I'd sure like to try a swizzle dog.
- I hate circuses.

831
01:09:03.703 --> 01:09:07.784
Nothing worse than a bunch of clowns
trying to make you laugh.

832
01:09:16.550 --> 01:09:20.251
- Look. a giraffe!
- Look. a fist!

833
01:09:24.517 --> 01:09:26.806
Clowns.

834
01:09:26.978 --> 01:09:29.896
Help! Help. let me out of here!

835
01:09:30.064 --> 01:09:33.813
I know you're out there! Help!

836
01:09:33.985 --> 01:09:38.279
Why isn't anybody doing anything?
I know you're out there!

837
01:09:44.246 --> 01:09:46.535
Let's go see the bearded lady.

838
01:09:46.707 --> 01:09:51.369
I seen too many of them in prison.
Stop bugging me or you're gonna get hurt.

839
01:09:51.545 --> 01:09:55.543
What did you say. you bow-tied freak?
Let him go!

840
01:09:56.718 --> 01:09:58.591
Forget it. big daddy!

841
01:09:58.761 --> 01:10:01.679
This is my show. I'm calling the shots.

842
01:10:01.848 --> 01:10:05.976
OK. we make a switch on the count of three.

843
01:10:06.144 --> 01:10:08.635
You toss the money and I release Junior.

844
01:10:08.814 --> 01:10:10.605
Fine.

845
01:10:10.774 --> 01:10:13.312
One. two. three!

846
01:10:13.861 --> 01:10:15.937
- Hey!
- Sucker!

847
01:10:16.113 --> 01:10:20.692
- Give me the boy!
- Why? He wants to go with me.

848
01:10:20.868 --> 01:10:25.993
How about it. kid? We'll go on a crime spree.
We'll terrorise the whole state.

849
01:10:26.165 --> 01:10:28.870
We'll eat smiley pies until we drop.

850
01:10:29.043 --> 01:10:31.451
What do you say?

851
01:10:33.256 --> 01:10:36.590
Come on. let's have some kicks. Tell-a-me.

852
01:10:36.760 --> 01:10:38.503
Tell-a-me.

853
01:10:38.678 --> 01:10:40.718
Yeah. kicks. good idea.

854
01:10:47.062 --> 01:10:50.099
- I'll tear you apart!
- Not while I'm around!

855
01:10:51.192 --> 01:10:53.481
Run. Junior. run!

856
01:10:53.653 --> 01:10:55.941
My money!

857
01:11:01.411 --> 01:11:03.487
Hold it!

858
01:11:03.663 --> 01:11:09.002
<i>The astounding Aslanian Family Tumblersl</i>

859
01:11:39.367 --> 01:11:41.360
Excuse me. lady!

860
01:11:44.414 --> 01:11:46.407
Ye-es!

861
01:11:56.969 --> 01:11:59.425
I'll get you now!

862
01:12:12.444 --> 01:12:15.196
Look out below!

863
01:12:16.573 --> 01:12:19.195
- Junior. are you OK?
- Yeah. I'm fine. Dad.

864
01:12:20.744 --> 01:12:25.205
- You called me Dad.
- Yeah. I guess I did.

865
01:12:29.963 --> 01:12:31.671
Stay away from...

866
01:12:31.839 --> 01:12:36.087
- He's getting away!
- Nobody messes with the Healys! Come on!

867
01:12:38.263 --> 01:12:40.968
There he is!

868
01:12:41.141 --> 01:12:44.842
<i>There's nothing like
going for an outing with your father.</i>

869
01:12:45.020 --> 01:12:47.974
- Look what I found!
- That's Roy's. Give me that.

870
01:12:48.148 --> 01:12:50.271
Why? You can't drive and shoot.

871
01:12:50.442 --> 01:12:52.934
- What do we do?
- I got an idea.

872
01:12:55.656 --> 01:12:59.025
- Go get him. Dad!
- Faster. son. faster!

873
01:12:59.202 --> 01:13:01.693
Attaboy!

874
01:13:01.871 --> 01:13:04.327
Shoot out his tyres. Dad!

875
01:13:05.375 --> 01:13:07.368
Don't mess with me!

876
01:13:09.504 --> 01:13:12.174
I demand you stop this car!

877
01:13:14.593 --> 01:13:16.586
<i>He's the wild one</i>

878
01:13:16.762 --> 01:13:18.636
What the hell is going on?

879
01:13:18.806 --> 01:13:22.056
- I want a divorce!
- Shut up. Flo!

880
01:13:38.618 --> 01:13:40.694
Wha...!

881
01:13:42.414 --> 01:13:44.739
Stop! Hit the brakes!

882
01:13:59.766 --> 01:14:02.601
Now what's going on? What's that smell?

883
01:14:04.145 --> 01:14:06.850
Well. Flo always said she wanted to travel.

884
01:14:09.818 --> 01:14:13.317
- Come on. let's go home.
- Move it.

885
01:14:16.617 --> 01:14:18.693
You little traitor!

886
01:14:18.869 --> 01:14:20.743
No!

887
01:14:25.835 --> 01:14:29.002
No!

888
01:14:31.090 --> 01:14:33.083
Daddy!

889
01:14:33.259 --> 01:14:37.589
Daddy. please don't go!
I'm sorry for all those bad things I did!

890
01:14:37.764 --> 01:14:42.058
If you come back. I promise
I'll never do anything naughty again.

891
01:14:42.227 --> 01:14:45.430
Daddy. come back! I love you!

892
01:14:47.399 --> 01:14:49.273
I love you. too. son.

893
01:14:49.443 --> 01:14:51.899
Dad? I don't believe it.

894
01:14:53.072 --> 01:14:55.230
I don't believe it either.

895
01:14:56.117 --> 01:14:58.442
- Are you gonna be OK?
- Yeah.

896
01:15:00.663 --> 01:15:03.237
But the prune's had it.

897
01:15:03.917 --> 01:15:07.083
- Lay still. Ambulance is on the way.
- I'll be all right.

898
01:15:07.253 --> 01:15:09.626
He got me in the prune.

899
01:15:10.382 --> 01:15:16.136
You're not gonna hold me to all that stupid
junk I said about being nice. are you?

900
01:15:16.305 --> 01:15:20.255
Of course not. I just want you to be yourself.

901
01:15:21.352 --> 01:15:23.973
Some people never learn.

902
01:15:24.146 --> 01:15:26.388
Come on. son.

903
01:15:41.540 --> 01:15:42.998
Come on.

904
01:15:44.167 --> 01:15:48.415
<i>Why does this guy love me?
Why do parents love any kid?</i>

905
01:15:48.589 --> 01:15:54.508
<i>It's one of those answers we'll never know
like "How high is up?". "Why is the sky blue?"</i>

906
01:15:54.678 --> 01:15:57.170
<i>and "Whatever happened to Mrs Healy?"</i>

907
01:15:57.348 --> 01:16:02.888
- Your pig's making funny noises.
- Big Miguel. he's got a bad stomach.

908
01:16:07.442 --> 01:16:09.518
Oh. my God!

909
01:16:10.612 --> 01:16:14.906
<i>Na-na-na-na-na
Na-na-na-na-na</i>

910
01:16:15.075 --> 01:16:16.450
<i>N- n-n-n-n-n-n-n</i>

911
01:16:16.618 --> 01:16:20.486
<i>Whoa-o-o-o-o</i>

912
01:16:20.664 --> 01:16:25.872
<i>Who wants to grow up?
Who wants responsibility?</i>

913
01:16:26.045 --> 01:16:29.414
<i>O- o-o-e-e-e</i>

914
01:16:30.925 --> 01:16:36.346
<i>Who wants to show up
At work until you're 93?</i>

915
01:16:36.514 --> 01:16:39.848
<i>Oh. no. not me</i>

916
01:16:41.269 --> 01:16:46.311
<i>Now. everybody says you're running wild</i>

917
01:16:46.483 --> 01:16:51.276
